## 4. AI Architecture — The Central Nervous System

Cactus is AI-native. AI is woven into the foundation, not
added as a feature later.

### The AI Service Module
All AI calls go through `src/core/ai/ai-service.ts`. This is
a clean interface so any model can be swapped without changing
business logic. Start with Anthropic Claude. Add orchestration
in Phase 2.

```typescript
// Always call AI through this interface, never directly
import { aiService } from '@/core/ai/ai-service';
const suggestion = await aiService.suggestMapping(rawHeaderName);
```

### Phase 1 AI Features (build now)
1. **Normalization Assistant:** When carrier_invoice_mappings
   has no match for a raw_header_name, call Claude to suggest
   the cactus_standard_field. Store as ai_suggested = TRUE with
   ai_confidence_score. Flag for human review before saving.
2. **Exception Flagging:** When a shipment_events row is inserted
   with an unexpected event_type (EXCEPTION, DAMAGED, LOST), AI
   analyzes context and sets ai_flagged = TRUE with ai_flag_reason.

### Phase 2 AI Features (design for, build later)
- Vector embeddings on carrier_invoice_mappings for semantic search
- Rate volatility prediction from rate_shop_log dataset
- Autonomous reconciliation with human-in-the-loop approval
- Carrier scorecard intelligence by lane

### The Shadow Ledger (rate_shop_log)
Log EVERY rate request — even rates the client doesn't select.
This builds the proprietary AI training dataset. Never skip
logging even if performance is a concern. Use async writes.

### Event Sourcing (shipment_events)
Never update a shipment status. Always append a new event row.
The current state of a shipment = the latest event in its timeline.

```typescript
// WRONG — destroys history
await supabase
  .from('shipment_ledger')
  .update({ status: 'DELIVERED' })
  .eq('id', shipmentId);

// RIGHT — preserves full timeline
await supabase
  .from('shipment_events')
  .insert({
    shipment_ledger_id: shipmentId,
    org_id: orgId,
    event_type: 'DELIVERED',
    carrier_timestamp: carrierData.timestamp,
    carrier_location: carrierData.location,
  });
```

### JSONB metadata columns
Every major table has a `metadata JSONB` column. Use it to store:
- Carrier-specific fields that don't fit typed columns
- WMS-provided context
- AI analysis results
- Raw webhook payloads for auditability

