## 5. Database Standards (v1.2.0)

### The 12 Tables

| Table | Purpose | AI Role |
|---|---|---|
| `organizations` | Multi-tenant root | Tenant scoping |
| `org_users` | Auth user → org mapping | RLS anchor |
| `rate_cards` | Markup rules per carrier | Source for margin analysis |
| `meters` | USPS wallet (cached balance) | — |
| `meter_transactions` | Immutable meter ledger | Cash flow patterns |
| `carrier_invoice_mappings` | Normalization layer | AI suggestion target |
| `shipment_ledger` | Single-Ceiling output | Billing source of truth |
| `cactus_invoices` | Weekly post-paid invoices | Auto-pull target |
| `locations` | Ship-from addresses | Phase 3 WMS foundation |
| `audit_logs` | Append-only action log | Compliance + AI audit |
| `rate_shop_log` | Shadow Ledger (ALL rates) | **Primary AI dataset** |
| `shipment_events` | Event sourcing timeline | **AI carrier intelligence** |

### Supported Carriers
`UPS` | `FEDEX` | `USPS` | `DHL_ECOM` | `DHL_EXPRESS` |
`UNIUNI` | `LANDMARK` | `ONTRAC` | `LSO`

### RLS Policy Pattern
Every table has exactly two policies:
1. `service_role` bypass — backend only, unrestricted
2. `org_members_read_own_*` — frontend, org-scoped reads only

