## 6. Product Architecture

### The Two Portals
**Cactus Portal** (client-facing)
Shows: shipments, tracking, meter balance, transaction history,
invoices, AI-powered insights (carrier recommendations, etc.)
Never shows: raw_carrier_cost, markup_percentage, markup_flat_fee,
pre_ceiling_amount, rate_cards data

**The Alamo** (internal Cactus admin)
Rate card management, carrier credentials, normalization mappings,
AI flag review queue, audit logs, billing overrides, global meter
health, carrier scorecard dashboard

### The Adapter Pattern
Every WMS/OMS/TMS connects through a dedicated adapter:
```
External System → Cactus Adapter → CactusCanonicalPayload → Engine
```
Adding a new integration = write one adapter. Core never changes.

### The Cactus Canonical Payload
```typescript
interface CactusCanonicalPayload {
  metadata: {
    tenantId: string;       // org UUID
    facilityId: string;     // location UUID
    correlationId: string;  // tracing across systems
    eventType: string;      // 'shipment.rated' | 'shipment.labeled'
    timestamp: string;      // ISO 8601 UTC
  };
  shipment: {
    origin: { addressId: string };
    destination: { address: AddressObject };
    packages: Array<{
      weight: { value: number; unit: 'lb' | 'oz' };
      dimensions: { l: number; w: number; h: number; unit: 'in' };
      lineItems: Array<{ sku: string; quantity: number }>;
    }>;
  };
  routing: {
    serviceLevel: string;
    carrierCode: string;
  };
}
```

